5. Bd7
6. Qxc4
6. Bc6{ The problem of the light-squared bishop is solved! }
7. Nf3( { After }7.Bxc6+ Nxc6 8.dxc5 Qd4 { , Black gets the pawn back. } )
7. Nd7
8. O-O
8. Ngf6
9. Nc3
9. Rc8( { 0-1 Vaulin-Shcherbakov, Elista 1997. The move }9...b5!? { is also possible, with multiple complications and an equal position according to the engines. } )( { After the text, Black is threatening }10.-- b5 { since }11.Nxb5? { is not possible in view of }11...Nb6 { followed }{ by ... c4  and White loses a piece. }{   }10.Qd3 { prevents that, but we can just }{ take on  d4 , exchange the light-squared bishops, and finish development with ... Be7  followed by ... O-O , with a good game ahead. } )
