6. cxd4{ Take the pawn, of course, and with normal development, Black is fine. }
7. Nxc4
7. Bc5{ Protecting the  d4 -pawn. }
8. O-O
8. Nge7
9. a3
9. a5
10. Qc2
10. O-O{ 0-1 Ponkratov-Vokhidov, St. Petersburg 2018. Ideas: ... Nf5 , ... b6 , ... Ba6 , etc. }
