9. c4( 9...Rc8 { is the other serious alternative for Black, but }9...c4 { is the best move in this position in my opinion. } )
10. Qd1
10. Rc8( { After this move, White has tried multiple options, and }11.Ne5 { is the most dangerous idea, in my opinion. } )
11. Re1
11. Be7
12. e4{ This is a very critical line, but if Black is well prepared, there shouldn't be any problems. }
12. O-O
13. d5( 13.a4 a6 { transposes to the main line }{ without the  a2  and  a7 -pawns, which is a worse version for White. } )
13. exd5
14. exd5
14. Nb4
15. d6( { The only dangerous move for Black, as after }15.Ne5 Bf5 { , White is in trouble! } )
15. Bxd6
16. Qxd6
16. Nc2{ The following variations are very sharp. }
17. Bg5{ A continuation that has been played in two games, but is a bad idea for White! }
17. Nxa1
18. Na3
18. Bg4{ The key move, with ... c3  coming in many variations! }
19. Qxd8
19. Rfxd8
20. Rxa1
20. c3( { Black is winning! The key is that after }21.bxc3 { , Black can play }21...Bxf3 { followed }{ by ... Rxc3  and there is a double attack against the bishop and knight! } )
