8. Rxd1
8. Bxc5
9. Nbd2( { The main move, but }9.Nfd2 { deserves consideration. } )
9. c3{ Forcing White to take on  c3 , breaking the structure. The good news is that our pawn structure will be slightly better. The bad news is that White can use the b-file along with the monster on  g2  to put pressure on the queenside and  b7  and  c6 . }
10. bxc3
10. O-O
11. Nb3( 11.Bb2 { transposes to the main lines. } )
11. Be7
