23. a5{ This is a forced line for both sides. }
24. Ke1{ An important move, defending  d2 . }
24. a4
25. Nc1{ The only move, of course. }
25. Rb2
26. Nd3
26. Rb8
27. Kd1
27. a3
28. Nc1{ The only move again. }
28. Rb2( { After }29.Ncb3 { , White has defended against the advance of the a-pawn with the knights and the king, but there is no progress possible to fight for a victory. } )
