18. Bf3( 18.exd5 { is strongly met with }18...Nxd4 { followed by ... Qxe2 , with a big advantage. } )
18. bxc3
19. Qxc3( 19.Rxb8 cxd2 { and Black is winning! } )
19. Rxb1
20. Rxb1
20. dxe4
21. Bxe4
21. Nxd4
22. Qxc4
22. Qe5{ Black is much better. The white pieces are in trouble and the knight on  d4  is simply the king of the dance floor. }
