9. cxd5{ This is a very concrete line. }
9. Nxc3
10. bxc3
10. exd5
11. Qb3{ The main line and complications are coming! }
11. Rd8{ Defending  d5  with ... c5  to follow if White does not push  c4 . }
12. c4{ The critical line and the chaos begins! }
12. Be6{ The move that has been giving Black the best results lately, sacrificing the  b7 -pawn. }
13. c5{ The main and best move in my opinion, closing the queenside, but Black can challenge the pawn structure with ... b6  on the next move. }
13. b6
14. Rc1( { Defending  c5 . }14.cxb6 axb6 { , }{ with ... c5  ideas, is very good for Black. } )
14. bxc5
15. Rxc5{ It makes sense to capture with the rook. It looks like Black is going to suffer along the c-file. Therefore, the next move is very very important! }
15. Nd7{ Black must take advantage of the lack of development on White's side. }
16. Rxc7( 16.Rb5? c6 17.Rb7 Rab8! { with a clear advantage for Black. } )
16. Rdb8
17. Qc2{ White must cover the two critical squares  b2  and  b1  at the same time! }
17. Qa3{ With the idea to play ... Rb2 . }
18. Bd3
18. Rb2{ A forced line. }
19. Qc3
19. Qxc3+
20. Rxc3
20. Rxa2{ With a balanced position. }
