9. Rc1( { The main line at this moment. A rare idea is }9.Nxe4 dxe4 10.Nd2 { and here, }10...f5 { , }{ defending  e4 , is a good move. }10...e5 { with some tricky ideas is good too, but I prefer }10...f5 { followed by ... e5  on the next move. } )
9. c6{ Defending  d5 , and now there are many options for White again. }
10. g4{ A super aggressive move. I faced this line against my friend and number 1 in Italy, the GM Vocaturo. The game now goes through complex and exciting paths. }( 10.h4 Rd8 11.g4 { transposes. } )
10. Nd7{ The most employed move. Black is getting ready to push the normal ... e5 . }
11. h4{ This is White's idea, to attack quickly with  g5 . }
11. Nxc3( 11...e5 { transposes to the main line with }12.cxd5 Nxc3 13.Rxc3 cxd5 { . } )
12. Rxc3
12. e5
13. cxd5( 13.g5 e4 14.Nd2 g6! { , blocking White's attack. } )
13. cxd5
14. g5{ We need to be careful now! }
14. e4{ The best move at this moment. }( 14...h5?! { I played this move against GM Vocaturo in Gibraltar 2019, but this isn't the best try }15.Be2 ( 15.Bb5 e4! 16.Bxd7 exf3! 17.Bxc8 Raxc8= { with a great initiative for Black. } )15...e4 16.Ng1! { A great improvement over my game, where Vocaturo played }16.Nd2 { . The knight is heading }{ to  f4 , which is a fantastic square! }{   }16...g6 17.Nh3± { and White's position is very comfortable. } )
15. Nd2
