9. c6{ Defending  d5 , and now there are many options for White again. }
10. Bd3{ The main line. }
10. Nxc3( 10...f5? { is a mistake because White has a good version of the Stonewall structure since the dark-squared bishop has been exchanged. } )
11. Rxc3
11. Nd7( 11...dxc4 { is another possibility for Black, but I prefer this move, not defining anything and being more flexible. } )
12. O-O{ The main line for White. }
12. e5( { Black threatens a fork on  e4 . That is why White cannot proceed with }13.cxd5 { . } )
13. dxe5( 13.Nxe5 Nxe5 14.dxe5 dxc4! { transposes to the main line. } )
13. dxc4( { An important move. Not }13...Nxe5 14.cxd5 cxd5 15.Be2 { and the  d5 -pawn is a disaster for Black. } )
14. Bxc4
14. Nxe5
15. Nxe5
15. Qxe5
16. f4( 16.Qe2 Bf5 { is not good for White. } )
16. Qf6( 16...Qe4 { is another possible move for Black. } )
17. e4
