3. Nf6
4. Bf4{ This is another rare but possible line. If we know our theory, we have great chances to get a better position out of the opening! }
4. dxc4( { Taking on  c4  is the best move, using the fact that White did not play   }4.Nc3 { and therefore cannot occupy the center }{ with  e4 . } )
5. Nc3{ Gambit style − Black must play ... c6  to proceed with ... b5  and defend the pawn! }
5. c6
6. a4{ Not allowing ... b5 . }
6. Bb4{ Insisting on ... b5 , and ... Nd5  is also coming! }
7. e3{ Not a dangerous move. Black proceeds with ... Nd5  and defends  b5 , with a healthy pawn up. }
7. Nd5
8. Rc1
8. Nxf4
9. exf4
9. b5
