13. g4( 13.O-O Re8 { , }{ with ... Bf8  and ... a5  ideas. Black has nothing to fear. } )
13. Bb4{ With a very interesting position for both players, but Black is not worse. It is very tough for White to open a file on the kingside. Naturally, the idea of ... Bb4  is to gain more control over the important  e4 -square, where a knight can jump in the near future. }( { After }14.gxh5 { , }{ we capture with the knight, and a possible plan is ... Re8  followed by ... Re6 , defending along the sixth rank. } )( { If }14.O-O-O { , we can play }14...Bxc3 { and after }15.bxc3 { , there is }15...h4! { , which is super strong. }{ Black closes the h-file and gets ready for ... Ne4  followed by ... Qa5 , with a strong attack. } )
