5. g6{ Black's idea is to play with ... Bf5 . This square is ideal for the bishop, as we already know. }
6. Bf4
6. Bf5
7. Qd2
7. Nf6
8. e3{ The main move. }
8. Nbd7
9. h3{ The main line, to move the bishop to  h2  if Black plays ... Nh5 . }
9. Nb6{ With the idea to play ... Bd6  or ... Ne4 . }
10. g4( 10.Nf3 { is not accurate because Black can play }10...Ne4!  )
10. Be6
11. f3{ And here, I like two alternatives for Black. }
11. Bd6( 11...h5!? { is another interesting idea for Black. } )
12. Qh2{ This is a forced line. }
12. Bxf4
13. Qxf4
13. Qe7{ With the idea to castle on the queenside and play ... Ne8 - d6 , with ... g5  and ... h5  ideas on the kingside, or bringing the rooks to the center. }
