7. f6{ This interesting move might come as a surprise to your opponent since it has barely been played. Black controls the  e5 -square and could expand with ... g5  and ... h5  if the bishop retreats to  g3 . }
8. Nbd2
8. g5
9. Be3
9. Nd6{ A very good move, not allowing the trade on  e4 . The  f5 -square is also very decent for the knight. }
10. c4
10. Be6
11. cxd5
11. Bxd5
12. Bd3
12. e6{ Black can play ... Qd7  or ... Qc7  and ... O-O-O  followed by ... Kb8 . Another plan is ... Nb4 , ... Bc6 , and ... Nd5 ; ... Nf5  is another possibility for Black. 0-1 Stavrianakis-Nikolaidis, Chalkida 2009. }
