[White "18) Colle Attack"]
[Black "Colle Attack 3.e3 − 5.c3 #1"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4
1. d5
2. Nf3
2. Nf6
3. e3( { The Colle or Zukertort System is here!   }4.c4 { on the next move transpose to the   }3.c4 { and  4.e3  lines. } )
3. e6
4. Bd3
4. c5( { This is an important moment for White. }5.c3 { , to play the Colle System, or }5.b3 { to play the Zukertort System. } )
5. c3{ A popular move in recent times in Spain by the popular superhero 'Rey Enigma'! }
5. b6{ I love this move. The idea is to play with ... Bb7  and ... Nbd7  quickly. Later, block with ... Ne4  if White's idea is to proceed with  Nbd2 ,  Re1 , or  Qe2  to push  e4 . }
6. O-O
6. Bb7
7. Nbd2
7. Nbd7
8. Re1{ The idea is to play  e4  on the next move, but Black can stop it. }
8. Ne4{ The capture on  e4  is always favorable for Black. Black's plan is to play with ... Bd6  and castle, and sometimes, ... f5  is possible, in the Stonewall spirit. }
9. Nf1{ With the idea to play  N3d2  and  f3 , but I think this is a slow plan for White. }
9. Bd6
10. N3d2
10. O-O
11. f3
11. Nef6{ Returning to the natural square. White wants to play  e4 , but Black can play ... e5  with the same idea, and White's pieces are oddly placed. }
12. e4
12. e5{ Dynamic play! }
13. f4{ This idea doesn't work, as the exchanges are in Black's favor. }
13. cxd4
14. cxd4
14. dxe4
15. Nxe4
15. Nxe4
16. Bxe4
16. Bxe4
17. fxe5( { The best line in my opinion for White, but Black's position is very pleasant. If White plays }17.Rxe4 Nf6 18.Re1 exd4 { ( }18...exf4 { is perfectly possible here too). } )
17. Nxe5
18. Rxe4
18. Ng6{ Black is slightly better; ... Qd7 , ... f5 , ... Rfe8 , ... Rac8  are just some ideas. }
