9. Ne5{ This is the main move in the Zukertort System. White's idea is to play with  f4  and  Qf3  or  Rf3 , and ideas with  g4 - g5  and  Qh3  or  Rh3 , to attack very fast on the kingside. }
9. Bb7
10. a3{ This move is recommended in  The Killer Colle-Zukertort System  course. }
10. Rc8{ White will most likely play  f4 , transposing to the lines covered after  10.f4  but we analyze now a couple of extra options. }
11. Qf3{ A very aggressive try. White brings the queen to the attack via  h3  or  g3 . Now there are a couple of interesting alternatives. }
11. Qc7{ Forcing White to make a decision with the  e5 -knight. White can decide now to make a draw or to play the text move. }( 11...a5 { is an option if you want to play for a win. }12.Qh3 cxd4 13.exd4 Ne7! { , with the idea of jumping }{ to the  e4 -square. }14.Rae1 h6= { (... Ne4  is possible in many variations anyway since the  c2 -pawn is hanging). } )
12. Qg3( 12.Nxc6 Bxc6 13.dxc5 bxc5 14.Bxf6 gxf6 15.Bxh7+ Kxh7 16.Qh5+= { leads to a perpetual. } )
12. cxd4
13. exd4
13. Ne7{ With the idea of going ... Nf5 , and I believe Black has an easier position to play. }
