9. Ne5{ This is the main move in the Zukertort System. White's idea is to play with  f4  and  Qf3  or  Rf3 , and ideas with  g4 - g5  and  Qh3  or  Rh3 , to attack very fast on the kingside. }
9. Bb7
10. f4
10. Rc8{ Black threatens ... cxd4  and ... Nb4 , hitting  c2  and  d3 . }
11. a3
11. Ne7{ The main idea. Black can play ... Ne4 , blocking the  d3 -bishop, or ... Nf5  and ... b5  is also in the air in certain positions where White goes  Qf3 . }
12. Qe2{ A normal idea for White. }
12. Ne4{ Blocking the  d3 -bishop. }
13. Nxe4( 13.Bxe4 dxe4 { is perfectly fine for Black, of course. } )( 13.Rad1 { is not accurate because Black can play }13...cxd4 14.exd4 Nc3! { winning the bishop pair, with a better position. } )( { Another alternative for White is }13.c4 cxd4 14.exd4 Nxd2 15.Qxd2 Nf5 { that was played in 0-1 Prisacaru-Iordachescu, Bucharest 2022, and Black had a dream position. } )
13. dxe4
14. Bc4( 14.Bb5 Nf5 { was played in 0-1 Milonakis-Favarel, Anogia 2017, and Black was much better. } )
14. cxd4
15. exd4( { The line with }15.Bxd4 Nf5 { was played in 0-1 Ratkovic-Perunovic, Belgrade 2015, and Black is better, of course! } )
15. Nf5
16. a4( 16.c3 Qh4!  )
16. Bxe5
17. dxe5( 17.fxe5 { is a serious mistake because }17...Nxd4 { wins a pawn. } )
17. Qc7{ Black has tremendous domination with ... Rfd8 , ... Qc5  plans and control of the d-file.  g4  is not good for White since the bishop on  b7  is too strong! }
