3. Bf4{ The famous Jobava-Rapport System. There are two quite interesting courses on Chessable: GM Niemann's and GM Simon William's courses, both with very creative ideas for White. }
3. a6( { I like this move, as I don't want to allow  Nb5 . }3...c5 { is a very playable option, obviously, but }4.e4 { is very interesting and tricky for Black. } )
4. e3
4. e6( { For the more adventurous, the aggressive }4...Bg4 { is also possible, but }4...e6 { is a safer move. } )
5. g4( { The main move, and the most aggressive! After }5.Nf3 c5 { , Black is fine following with normal development. } )
5. Bb4( { The main line, and here, }6.Ne2 { is the only option for White to fight for an advantage. } )
6. Nge2
6. h6( 6...Nxg4 { is not possible since }7.Rg1 { is very strong. } )
7. a3{ This is Niemann's idea in his Jobava-Rapport Chessable course. }
7. Be7
8. h4{ An interesting variation, and with very crazy conclusions. }
8. Nxg4
9. Ng3( 9.Rg1 { is not accurate because Black has }9...h5 { and  f3  isn't possible. } )
9. Nf6
10. Nh5
10. g6
11. Nxf6+
