5. Bb4( { The main line, and here, }6.Ne2 { is the only option for White to fight for an advantage. } )
6. Nge2
6. h6( 6...Nxg4 { is not possible since }7.Rg1 { is very strong. } )
7. a3{ This is Niemann's idea in his Jobava-Rapport Chessable course. }
7. Be7
8. Nc1( 8.h3 c5 { is the best move, hitting the center. } )
8. c5
9. dxc5
9. Nfd7{ A great move for Black, to recapture on  c5  with the knight. }
10. Nd3
10. Nxc5
11. Nxc5
11. Bxc5
12. Qf3( { If White plays }12.Bd3 { or }12.Bg2 { , Black can play }12...Nc6 { followed by ... Bd7  and long castle. } )
12. Nc6
13. O-O-O{ We will also go to the 'East' part of the board since White's attack is also very fast on the kingside. }
13. Bd7
14. h4
14. Qa5{ And long castle on the next move! }
